what is node?

type down in node.js cmd
    node -v                                     (node version)
    node                                        (opening to node.js)
    console.log('Hello world');                 (print hello world to the screen)
    window                                      (chrome v8 console)
    global                                      (^ in node.js. pathing and cmds for node.js. just like "window" ^)
    #document                                   (chrome v8 console)
    process                                     (^ in node.js. pathing and cmds for node.js. just like "#document" ^)
    process.exit(0)                             (exit cmd prompt with zero error)
    ctl + C twice                               (to exit, press ^C again or type .exit)